<br>
<br>
Bath time was alway fun, you should see the evil piggie looks I got when they were soaking wet huddled in the tub. <br>
<br>
 They're really much better about it then they used to be. I have one who doesn't do anything but bite me, only she doesn't bite hard, she just grabs my finger with her teeth and pulls my hand away from her feet.  Other than that she's perfectly well behaved.  <br>
<br>
The one with all the fur is the one who keeps pulling his feet in so I can't find them.  Once I finally get them clear of all his fur, he just yanks them back in, once I had to clipper him bald to get to his toe nails.....he was NOT happy....poor thing shook and cringed the whole time.<br>
<br>
But our third one is a devil pig, he has red eyes and I swear he knows how to angle them in the light so they flash red.  He just chatters his teeth and threatens to bite the entire time I'm trying to grab a paw, any paw....it usually takes bout ten tries to get him fully clipped.<br>
<br>
I only wish they had scruffs I could grab!  Oh well time to feed the piggies, they're hoping around and doing they're hungry dance.<br>
<br>
~mirr.<br>
