<br>
My African Grey, Lazarus...SCREAMS.<br>
<br>
Best results were toweling him (which he'd still rip through the towel with his beak!) and doing it as quickly as possible.<br>
<br>
I was lucky enough to find a line of roughened cement perches. These naturally buff their talons, so it really eliminated the need for me to clip his nails.<br>
<br>
I also had it professionally done one time at the vet. The vet did a horrible job. 90% of his nails were bleeding so heavily that they couldn't stop the bleeding for a time, and finally needed to apply medication to stop it. They also did a horrendous job on the wing clipping.<br>
<br>
Greys are neurotic enough as it is, and he started feather picking as a result. I had to put him on medication (basically bird anti-depressants) to stop the feather picking while they grew back in. He hasn't been clipped since and has full flight feathers which means no more outdoor trips for now.<br>
